IN	2 tablespoons  olive oil
IN	1 tablespoon  lime juice
IN	1/4 teaspoon  salt
IN	1/8 teaspoon  pepper
IN	1 pound  skinless orange roughy or red snapper fillets, cut into 1-inch cubes
IN	1 cup  chopped onion
IN	1 cup  chopped green sweet pepper
IN	6 cloves  garlic, minced (1 tablespoon)
IN	1   jalapeno pepper, seeded and finely chopped
IN	1 14-1/2-ounce can  diced tomatoes
IN	1/2 cup  unsweetened coconut milk
IN	8 ounces  peeled and deveined uncooked medium shrimp
IN	1/2 cup  snipped cilantro
IN	2 cups  hot cooked rice
IN	2 tablespoons  snipped fresh cilantro
IN	  Bottled hot pepper sauce (optional)
PR	1. In a medium bowl stir together 1 tablespoon of the olive oil, lime juice, salt, and pepper. Add fish cubes; toss to coat. Set aside.
PR	2. In a 3-quart saucepan heat remaining oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion, sweet pepper, garlic, and jalapeno. Cook and stir 4 minutes until onion is tender but not brown. Stir in undrained tomatoes and coconut milk. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in shrimp, fish mixture, and 1/2 cup cilantro. Return to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until fish just flakes easily with a fork and shrimp turn opaque, stirring occasionally. Serve over hot cooked rice. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Pass hot pepper sauce, if desired. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
